OL,3,CHow could conflict in the Middle East
OL,4,Caffect your bills at home?
OL,6,FRising oil costs mean it will cost
OL,7,Fmore to transport and ship products,
OL,8,Fwhich, coupled with disruptions to
OL,9,Fsupply routes, could filter through to
OL,10,Fprices at the till in the months to
OL,11,Fcome.
OL,13,FCrude oil is also used in many
OL,14,Ffertilisers, which are used to grow
OL,15,Ffood and are vital to the global food
OL,16,Fchain. Without them, crop yields would
OL,17,Fdecline sharply. Around a quarter of
OL,18,Fthe fertiliser used to grow food has
OL,19,Fto travel through the Strait of Hormuz.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31114
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1772817079
OL,3,CHow could conflict in the Middle East
OL,4,Caffect your bills at home?
OL,6,FThe countries currently affected by
OL,7,Fconflict are also significant
OL,8,Fproducers of dates, olive oil, nuts
OL,9,Fand spices such as saffron.
OL,11,FAll of this depends on how long the
OL,12,Fconflict goes on for. Some experts say
OL,13,Fthat if it's short-lived, the economy
OL,14,Fcould weather the storm.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
