OL,3,CHow could conflict in the Middle East
OL,4,Caffect your bills at home?
OL,6,FThere is also the Energy Price Cap,
OL,7,Fwhich sets the limit on the amount
OL,8,Fthat energy suppliers can charge
OL,9,Fcustomers on standard variable tariffs
OL,10,Ffor gas and electricity. This means
OL,11,Fmany will be protected from volatile
OL,12,Fspikes in energy costs. But if this
OL,13,Fconflict continues, it is likely the
OL,14,FPrice Cap rate will go up in July,
OL,15,Fmaking life more expensive for
OL,16,Fthousands of households in the country.
OL,18,FWhat about mortgage rates?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/20
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
